Description: Model of a rectangular mud brick; part of a foundation-deposit. The surface of the large sides is slightly hollow due to the modelling by hand.
Authority: Ruler: Psamtek I (from context of the find)
Findspot: Found/Acquired: Tell Dafana, "Qasr", casemate building A, beneath the NE corner (or SE corner)
Curator's comments: see also one in Cairo, EM, JE 27385
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (p. 54 § 52, p. 54-55 § 54, pl. xxii, 12, xxiii)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.54, p.175, pl.17, p.244, pl.86)
Condition: good; broken in four fragments reunited (drawing in original publication shows already cracks)
